item.description:
Netmiko is a very popular open-source Python library written by a network engineer for network engineers to &ldquo;simplify CLI connections to network devices.&rdquo;
It supports a variety of platforms and is a great tool for network engineers to learn how Python can be used to interact with their infrastructure.
What you’ll Learn  How to connect to an IOS-XE device with Netmiko How to send show commands to the IOS-XE Device How to send configuration commands to the IOS-XE Device Call to Action  What you&rsquo;ll need  Access to a Sandbox with Netmiko installed and an IOS-XE Device Text editor (such as VS Code) to remotely edit files on the jump host or your local Netmiko installation.
